<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Diesel Engine Diagnostic Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Engine Symptoms
        Diagnostics - Problems and Conditions - Fuel in Coolant
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="4">
        <title>Fuel in Coolant</title>
        <para id="s27004004">
            <title>Symptom</title>
        </para>
        <para>Coolant contaminated with diesel fuel will have a diesel fuel odor.</para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <title>Cause</title>
            <item>
                <para>Leaking or cracked injector sleeve with injector O-ring failure</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Cracked or porous head casting in fuel rail cross-drillings.</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <title>Tools</title>
            <item>
                <para>Regulated compressed air</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Fuel Test Fitting</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Fuel/Oil Pressure Test Coupler</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Cylinder head test plate</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Water supply housing pressure adapter</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Thermostat opening pressure adapter (cylinder head)</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <para>
            <title>Procedure</title>
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Verify coolant contamination.</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Check for diesel fuel odor in coolant.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Coolant may be discolored if diesel fuel is present.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Be sure to place a rag or suitable container under the fuel pressure test valve when bleeding
                        the fuel rail. Dispose of fuel in a correct container clearly marked DIESEL FUEL according to
                        local regulations.
                    </para>
                </caution>
                <note>
                    <para>Engine fuel can be a threat to the environment. Never dispose of engine fuel by putting it in
                        the trash, pouring on the ground, in the sewers, in streams, or bodies of water.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Plug in the cylinder block heater to warm coolant.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death and damage to the engine:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Always allow the engine to cool for 15 minutes.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Wrap a thick cloth around the cap.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Loosen cap slowly a quarter to half turn.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Pause for a moment to avoid water or steam scalding.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Continue to turn the cap and remove.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Never add cold coolant to a hot engine. This can result in a cracked cylinder head or
                            crankcase.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Never use water as a coolant substitute.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f27004" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh05/H05004.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Deaeration tank fill position</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Deaeration tank cap</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Deaeration tank</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">MAXIMUM coolant level mark</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">ADD coolant level mark</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove cap from deaeration tank and fill with coolant to a level above the deaeration inlet
                line to tank.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f27004" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh11/H11060.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Shrader valve assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Center stem</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f27004" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh11/H11061.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Diagnostic coupling</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Center section</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Engines are equipped with a fuel pressure test valve in the form of either a Shrader valve or a
                    diagnostic coupling.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pressurize fuel rail with air from the fuel pressure test valve on the intake manifold to
                550 kPa to 690 kPa (80 psi to 100 psi) using the fuel line test adapter. Observe deaeration tank for air
                bubbles.
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>If air bubbles appear in deaeration tank, do step 5.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>If air bubbles do not appear in deaeration tank, do step 6.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f27004" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh31/H31381.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Injector cut-away with injector sleeve</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove all injectors and inspect O-rings and injector sleeves for damage.</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>If any injector O-ring or injector sleeve appears damaged, clean the injector and replace
                        O-rings or injector sleeves. Test the system again. Do step 4.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>If injector O-rings or injector cups are not damaged, do step 6.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove, inspect, and pressurize the cylinder head following the procedure in the Engine
                Service Manual.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
